Hello @Endex  and @soulrebel!   After a fresh night a sleep I have reviewed everything again.  Like mentioned by @Endex , I delete the subtensor docker an reinstall all again... but it was still not working.  And I did it again and again, until I notice that even after removing everything about my docker installation (via... docker prune -a)... the docker subtensor volume was still present... with the persistent data in it... most likely corrupted.  Once I have remove that volume... and did again the docker reinstall of everything... it worked... at last!  Now it is not syncing forever... but I got the zzZZ Idle... Now my balance on the local subtensor matches the balance on finney.   Now I was able to run the miner bind on the local subtensor!  And now... after 30 minutes of running... I have not seen any errors or timeouts!   Thanks to both of you @Endex and @soulrebel for sharing your thoughts, your experiences and knowledge.  Long live to this wonderful community that is Bittensor!  Cheers!

I think many people tend to forget how a miner’s network can affect their scoring. A sudden drop in network bandwidth can very quickly affect scoring and cause a “random” dereg

miners should be able to submit an arbitrary number of machine proofs at any given time. Then they wont need more UIDs for more incentive.
Their score just becomes a function of how many machines they bring the network
yet this needs to be validated with pow otherwise people fake it
Exactly which is why we implemented POW that supports multiple gpus then the next step is scoring miners based on the number of gpus
Hmmm… interesting. That way we can effectively multiply the available gpus without increasing the amount of UIDS
